Unplug him!

1026
01:07:45.761 --> 01:07:47.596
It's a matter of national security.

1027
01:07:47.763 --> 01:07:49.599
Let me talk to him first.

1028
01:07:52.977 --> 01:07:55.270
Hello, Dr. Elefun.
- Hello, Toby.

1029
01:07:55.646 --> 01:07:58.774
Toby? Nobody has called me
that for a while.

1030
01:07:58.857 --> 01:08:00.984
This isn't your fault, you know?

1031
01:08:01.151 --> 01:08:02.570
You're fantastic.

1032
01:08:02.736 --> 01:08:06.115
Absolutely first class, superb, wonderful.

1033
01:08:06.198 --> 01:08:07.366
Thank you.

1034
01:08:07.491 --> 01:08:10.452
You know, I tried to find
my place in the world.

1035
01:08:10.619 --> 01:08:12.913
I... I thought
I'd found it.

1036
01:08:13.079 --> 01:08:16.624
But I guess fitting in can be
a lot more complicated than it seems. huh?

1037
01:08:16.665 --> 01:08:19.084
Dear boy, if you only knew...

1038
01:08:19.459 --> 01:08:22.422
I think maybe, this is
what supposed to happen.

1039
01:08:22.714 --> 01:08:24.716
This is my destiny.

1040
01:08:26.259 --> 01:08:28.553
Buhuhu.

1041
01:08:28.678 --> 01:08:32.555
It's a machine, come on,
let's get moving people.

1042
01:08:32.722 --> 01:08:34.850
This is wrong, Tenma, you know it.

1043
01:08:35.016 --> 01:08:39.521
The President is right.
It's just a machine!

1044
01:08:40.689 --> 01:08:42.274
Goodbye, Dr. Elefun.

1045
01:08:42.983 --> 01:08:44.583
Load the blue core into The Peacekeeper.

1046
01:08:44.609 --> 01:08:47.570
I got a press conference
scheduled in ten minutes.

1047
01:09:29.109 --> 01:09:30.402
I'm sorry.

1048
01:09:30.735 --> 01:09:31.904
Don't be.

1049
01:09:32.154 --> 01:09:35.281
I'm sorry, I couldn't have been
a better Toby for you...

1050
01:09:36.115 --> 01:09:37.700
dad.

1051
01:09:40.829 --> 01:09:43.790
Well, Tenma.
Is it done?

1052
01:09:47.877 --> 01:09:49.587
It's done.

1053
01:09:55.843 --> 01:09:57.011
Good man.

1054
01:09:57.177 --> 01:10:00.013
When I'm re-elected,
you can have the funding...

1055
01:10:00.055 --> 01:10:03.015
to make as many little toys as you want.

1056
01:10:03.558 --> 01:10:04.976
No!

1057
01:10:05.728 --> 01:10:08.146
If you want the core,
you're gonna have to kill me.

1058
01:10:09.647 --> 01:10:11.943
Tenma!
- No! I created the core.

1059
01:10:12.110 --> 01:10:13.527
They're gonna have to kill me.

1060
01:10:13.736 --> 01:10:16.863
Well, I think Metro City can learn
to cope without you.

1061
01:10:16.946 --> 01:10:18.239
Hand it over.

1062
01:10:20.157 --> 01:10:21.992
It appears, I don't have it!

1063
01:10:22.159 --> 01:10:23.577
Tenma!

1064
01:10:26.998 --> 01:10:28.999
Tenma, open this!

1065
01:10:30.251 --> 01:10:31.836
Open that door!

1066
01:10:32.544 --> 01:10:34.379
Oh, please.

1067
01:10:38.300 --> 01:10:40.009
I said, open that door!

1068
01:10:40.176 --> 01:10:42.179
Never!
- Now!

1069
01:10:44.556 --> 01:10:45.557
Lost.

1070
01:10:45.724 --> 01:10:48.683
If you want something done right,
you gotta do it yourself.

1071
01:10:54.022 --> 01:10:56.442
Wow! What...
what are you doing?

1072
01:10:56.776 --> 01:10:58.486
You may not be Toby...

1073
01:10:58.570 --> 01:11:00.154
but you're still my son.

1074
01:11:00.404 --> 01:11:01.698
Dad.

1075
01:11:06.159 --> 01:11:08.578
Now, fly.
Fly!

1076
01:11:17.128 --> 01:11:19.964
No!
No!

1077
01:11:21.925 --> 01:11:24.760
Arrest them immediately.
I want them shot for treason.

1078
01:11:25.010 --> 01:11:27.570
We're gonna have to use the Peacemaker
to get the blue core back.

1079
01:11:27.680 --> 01:11:29.057
Don't use the red core.

1080
01:11:29.099 --> 01:11:31.392
The negative energy,
we can't know how it will behave.

1081
01:11:31.559 --> 01:11:34.687
After many conflicts between
positive and negative energy...

1082
01:11:34.812 --> 01:11:36.814
the negative always prevails.

1083
01:11:36.980 --> 01:11:39.273
Look at Human history.
Look at me.

1084
01:11:39.356 --> 01:11:40.775
My point, excat!

1085
01:11:40.858 --> 01:11:42.651
Turn this thing on.
- I won't.

1086
01:11:42.693 --> 01:11:44.904
I have 50 reporters waiting outside!

1087
01:11:44.946 --> 01:11:47.575
Turn it on.
- You don't understand the technology!

1088
01:11:47.616 --> 01:11:48.784
Technology?

1089
01:11:48.826 --> 01:11:50.660
Who cares about technology?

1090
01:11:50.702 --> 01:11:52.412
Who understands technology?

1091
01:11:52.453 --> 01:11:55.081
It's a robot, it will do what I say.

1092
01:11:56.998 --> 01:11:58.833
Red core loaded.

1093
01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:01.003
You ready to do as you're told?

1094
01:12:01.170 --> 01:12:03.172
You ready to rock and roll?

1095
01:12:03.213 --> 01:12:04.214
Sir?

1096
01:12:04.422 --> 01:12:08.802
Destroy the boy robot,
bring back the blue core.

1097
01:12:12.764 --> 01:12:13.932
What are you? Deaf?

1098
01:12:14.098 --> 01:12:16.518
I told you to destroy the boy robot...

1099
01:12:18.687 --> 01:12:21.648
And bring back the blue core.

1100
01:12:21.939 --> 01:12:23.941
Everybody out!
Now!

1101
01:12:25.235 --> 01:12:26.235
Move it!

1102
01:12:33.867 --> 01:12:35.160
Uh, sorry, guys...

1103
01:12:35.201 --> 01:12:38.164
I'm getting word that President Stone
may be slightly delayed.

1104
01:12:47.797 --> 01:12:49.382
Is this thing on?

1105
01:12:51.634 --> 01:12:53.344
What? Where are you going?

1106
01:12:53.511 --> 01:12:56.346
Come back!
- Monster, stand down!

1107
01:12:56.471 --> 01:12:58.891
By order of President Stone.

1108
01:13:02.479 --> 01:13:05.731
This is the life, buddy.
Smooth sail.

1109
01:13:08.150 --> 01:13:10.152
Sorry, guys.
- Oh, no!

1110
01:13:10.235 --> 01:13:14.447
It's that crazy flying kid again!
- I'm a robot, just like you.

1111
01:13:15.114 --> 01:13:16.564
What are you doing all the way out here?

1112
01:13:16.574 --> 01:13:19.119
We got tried of the rat-race.
We dropped out.

1113
01:13:19.161 --> 01:13:21.995
We're trying to live more naturally,
you know, like real birds.

1114
01:13:23.664 --> 01:13:26.083
What's that?
- You know what humans are like!

1115
01:13:26.208 --> 01:13:29.170
New Year's? 4th of July?
Mother's Day?

1116
01:13:29.337 --> 01:13:31.630
We gotta do something!
- What? Help the humans?

1117
01:13:31.714 --> 01:13:33.131
We are robots.
It's not our problem.

1118
01:13:33.173 --> 01:13:36.302
Yeah, forget about them.
What ever they did for us?

1119
01:13:43.433 --> 01:13:44.434
He's right.

1120
01:13:44.517 --> 01:13:47.144
According to the laws of robotics,
we gotta go help.

1121
01:13:47.686 --> 01:13:51.899
A Squeezy bottle's gotta do,
what a Squeezy bottle's gotta do.

1122
01:13:57.446 --> 01:13:59.573
<i>Where you are?</i>

1123
01:14:08.457 --> 01:14:12.001
<i>Where are you, robot boy?</i>

1124
01:14:15.713 --> 01:14:17.131
Oh, no!

1125
01:14:21.387 --> 01:14:23.221
There you are.

1126
01:14:33.980 --> 01:14:35.565
What?
But...

1127
01:14:36.483 --> 01:14:38.068
Huh, cool!

1128
01:14:50.287 --> 01:14:51.873
That has to be Astro.

1129
01:14:51.998 --> 01:14:53.708
I don't care if he's a robot.

1130
01:14:53.875 --> 01:14:56.169
I miss him.
- I hear ya.

1131
01:14:59.130 --> 01:15:02.091
When the going gets tough,
smart people take a hike.

1132
01:15:02.174 --> 01:15:03.466
Bye-bye, kids.

1133
01:15:03.966 --> 01:15:05.552
What do you want?
An apology?

1134
01:15:05.635 --> 01:15:09.723
Nope, just the car.
- I would love oblige you, but...

1135
01:15:12.768 --> 01:15:15.604
Come on, I love you, guys.
Please.

1136
01:15:16.313 --> 01:15:18.148
Freaking robots!

1137
01:15:22.902 --> 01:15:23.903
Gotcha!

1138
01:15:32.786 --> 01:15:35.206
The city elected me!

1139
01:15:35.372 --> 01:15:38.208
I own it.
It's mine!

1140
01:15:47.842 --> 01:15:49.718
Hey! I'm voting for
the other guy!

1141
01:15:49.761 --> 01:15:50.762
What?

1142
01:15:57.101 --> 01:15:59.102
Thank you.
Anytime you need me.

1143
01:16:12.657 --> 01:16:13.950
What?

1144
01:16:15.577 --> 01:16:18.955
I got machine guns... in my butt?

1145
01:16:21.498 --> 01:16:22.917
You gotta be kidding me.

1146
01:16:23.042 --> 01:16:24.335
Batter up!

1147
01:16:28.840 --> 01:16:30.675
Homerun!

1148
01:16:50.192 --> 01:16:52.486
Astro?
- Cora!

1149
01:16:53.571 --> 01:16:54.989
Thanks, guys.

1150
01:16:55.156 --> 01:16:57.159
Hey, who's driving?

1151
01:17:05.165 --> 01:17:07.000
Trash can, faster!

1152
01:17:08.376 --> 01:17:09.669
Move over!

1153
01:17:35.568 --> 01:17:37.862
Are we going up?
- No, the city is falling down.

1154
01:17:37.903 --> 01:17:41.575
Cora, I've to take care of this.
- Astro, no.

1155
01:17:42.158 --> 01:17:43.452
Astro!

1156
01:17:49.666 --> 01:17:50.959
Look.

1157
01:18:03.720 --> 01:18:06.014
Fighting comrades, to arms!

1158
01:18:06.140 --> 01:18:07.725
I've got three arms.

1159
01:18:23.448 --> 01:18:24.449
Where is he?

1160
01:18:24.616 --> 01:18:27.450
Is he really be okay?
- I hope so.

1161
01:18:33.458 --> 01:18:35.167
Hey, ugly!

1162
01:18:36.001 --> 01:18:37.295
Down here.

1163
01:18:37.670 --> 01:18:40.339
We demand immediately that
you cease oppressing...

1164
01:18:40.380 --> 01:18:41.965
our Comrade Astro.

1165
01:18:42.048 --> 01:18:44.050
We may not be allowed to harm humans...

1166
01:18:44.091 --> 01:18:44.967
but there's nothing that say...

1167
01:18:45.009 --> 01:18:48.679
we can't do some
serious damage to a monster.

1168
01:18:48.721 --> 01:18:50.432
Aye, comrades?

1169
01:18:53.976 --> 01:18:55.686
Oh, look over there.

1170
01:18:57.439 --> 01:19:01.317
Where are you, robot boy?
I know you're still alive.

1171
01:19:01.567 --> 01:19:03.569
You can't hide from...

1172
01:19:07.781 --> 01:19:09.366
That all you got?

1173
01:19:17.332 --> 01:19:18.499
Come here!

1174
01:19:21.627 --> 01:19:25.715
The party's over, kid.
Blue core obtained.

1175
01:19:46.693 --> 01:19:47.861
Toby!

1176
01:19:49.280 --> 01:19:50.447
Dad.

1177
01:19:51.739 --> 01:19:54.701
I don't understand.
Why didn't it absorb me?

1178
01:19:54.784 --> 01:19:55.785
Because it can't.

1179
01:19:55.868 --> 01:19:59.413
If the red and blue core
come together, well...

1180
01:19:59.664 --> 01:20:01.248
you both die.

1181
01:20:02.624 --> 01:20:05.294
Come on, son, we need to get far away.

1182
01:20:06.129 --> 01:20:07.837
Where are you, Astro?

1183
01:20:10.089 --> 01:20:12.717
Where is your robot friend?
Where is he?

1184
01:20:14.094 --> 01:20:17.638
I got an election to win.
And I want that core.

1185
01:20:21.268 --> 01:20:23.270
Where is he hiding?
Tell me!

1186
01:20:23.478 --> 01:20:25.480
You hear me?
Where is he?

1187
01:20:25.771 --> 01:20:28.607
We have to go.
- This is it.

1188
01:20:29.149 --> 01:20:31.150
This is what I was created for.

1189
01:20:31.276 --> 01:20:33.695
This... is my destiny.

1190
01:20:33.862 --> 01:20:35.030
Toby, now!

1191
01:20:35.197 --> 01:20:37.491
I'm sorry, but this is who I am.

1192
01:20:37.992 --> 01:20:39.536
Onward and upward...

1193
01:20:40.453 --> 01:20:41.328
Dad.

1194
01:20:41.453 --> 01:20:42.620
No!

1195
01:20:44.373 --> 01:20:46.666
Huh, you're back for more?

1196
01:20:54.215 --> 01:20:56.842
Wait, wait!
No-no... wait, wait!

1197
01:21:00.345 --> 01:21:01.512
No!

1198
01:21:11.816 --> 01:21:13.525
My son.
- Dad.

1199
01:21:20.489 --> 01:21:22.616
Get out of me.
No!

1200
01:21:23.827 --> 01:21:25.411
Get out!

1201
01:21:25.870 --> 01:21:27.996
Get us out of here.
- I'm trying.

1202
01:21:30.167 --> 01:21:31.876
No! No!

1203
01:21:33.627 --> 01:21:35.461
Oh, nuts!

1204
01:21:44.012 --> 01:21:45.305
Son.

1205
01:22:06.324 --> 01:22:07.784
Guards, seize this girl immediately!

1206
01:22:07.867 --> 01:22:09.828
She kicked me.
She kept kicking me.

1207
01:22:09.870 --> 01:22:12.163
President Stone, sir.
You're under arrest.

1208
01:22:12.247 --> 01:22:15.500
No, you can't do this to me.
I got an election to win.

1209
01:22:15.709 --> 01:22:17.085
Astro?
- Astro?

1210
01:22:17.210 --> 01:22:19.629
Astro?
- Astro?

1211
01:22:22.507 --> 01:22:24.217
Astro!

1212
01:22:26.719 --> 01:22:28.304
Oh, no!

1213
01:22:31.265 --> 01:22:33.267
Oh, Astro.

1214
01:22:34.185 --> 01:22:37.020
Who was he?
- That robot saved the Metro city.

1215
01:22:37.104 --> 01:22:38.521
Why would he care?

1216
01:22:38.688 --> 01:22:41.233
Because that robot had more humanity...

1217
01:22:41.316 --> 01:22:42.901
than most of us.

1218
01:22:43.317 --> 01:22:45.737
Who are you?
- I'm a friend of his.

1219
01:22:45.988 --> 01:22:48.949
From the surface.
- You're from the surface?

1220
01:22:53.745 --> 01:22:56.873
Can you fix him?
- No. I'm afraid, no.

1221
01:22:57.039 --> 01:22:59.667
His blue core was unique.

1222
01:23:00.334 --> 01:23:03.795
Now it's died with him.
- It's not fair.

1223
01:23:03.962 --> 01:23:05.798
All he ever did was help people.

1224
01:23:05.881 --> 01:23:07.882
Not just people.

1225
01:23:09.592 --> 01:23:11.597
Astro brought Zog back to life.

1226
01:23:11.680 --> 01:23:14.306
How?
- The blue stuff.

1227
01:23:15.140 --> 01:23:18.393
Do... do you have any of that
blue stuff left?

1228
01:23:19.644 --> 01:23:22.605
Do you think, you could spare
some for our friend here?

1229
01:23:58.181 --> 01:23:59.348
Dad!

1230
01:23:59.473 --> 01:24:00.641
Cora!

1231
01:24:00.976 --> 01:24:03.103
What happened?
Is the Peacekeeper gone?

1232
01:24:03.145 --> 01:24:04.437
Yes.

1233
01:24:09.107 --> 01:24:11.234
But... How am I still...

1234
01:24:15.865 --> 01:24:18.700
Thank you, Zog.
- No big deal.

1235
01:24:26.832 --> 01:24:27.833
Astro...

1236
01:24:27.916 --> 01:24:31.296
I think you finally found
your place in the world.

1237
01:24:31.463 --> 01:24:35.675
You are a hero.
A robot with the heart of a lion.

1238
01:24:35.758 --> 01:24:37.760
And everyone finally knows it.

1239
01:24:45.225 --> 01:24:47.853
I love happy endings.

1240
01:24:48.562 --> 01:24:50.563
Would you?
- Sure.

1241
01:24:50.897 --> 01:24:52.065
Thanks.

1242
01:24:52.607 --> 01:24:54.193
Cora?

1243
01:24:54.526 --> 01:24:56.110
Cora!
- Cora!

1244
01:24:56.277 --> 01:24:58.695
Mom? Dad?
- Where have you been, sweetie?

1245
01:24:58.779 --> 01:25:01.408
We've searched high and low for you.
- Really?

1246
01:25:06.453 --> 01:25:08.581
Viva la robot revolution!

1247
01:25:09.081 --> 01:25:11.082
It's looks-like all the
interesting stuff's over.

1248
01:25:11.124 --> 01:25:14.085
How typical! Just typical.
- Thanks for your help, guys.

1249
01:25:14.126 --> 01:25:17.256
Oh, it was nothing.
- Yeah, when you think about it, Sparxy.

1250
01:25:17.297 --> 01:25:19.591
It really was nothing.

1251
01:25:19.675 --> 01:25:21.802
Are you trying to upset me?

1252
01:25:22.969 --> 01:25:25.263
Will you be wanting the car, sir?

1253
01:25:25.346 --> 01:25:28.182
I don't want you to
call me "Sir" anymore, Orrin.

1254
01:25:28.224 --> 01:25:29.808
In fact, take the day off.

1255
01:25:29.891 --> 01:25:33.437
Go on and enjoy yourself
with the robot ladies.

1256
01:25:33.854 --> 01:25:35.981
Thank you, Dr. Tenma.

1257
01:25:36.023 --> 01:25:37.732
Call me Bill.

1258
01:25:39.693 --> 01:25:41.695
I'm so freaked right now.

1259
01:25:46.658 --> 01:25:47.951
Everybody, take cover!

1260
01:25:47.993 --> 01:25:49.994
We're under an alien attack!

1261
01:25:52.164 --> 01:25:54.791
Wait! Are you sure
you're ready for this, Astro?

1262
01:25:54.874 --> 01:25:56.875
I was made ready!

